
@startuml
' Define classes

class Bus {
  -id: int
  -lineNumber: String
  -currentTrajectory: Trajectory
}

class Line {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -category: Category
  -trajectories: Set<Trajectory>
}

class Trajectory {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -status: Status (approved, suspended, cancelled)
  -approvalHistory: List<ApprovalRequest>
  -startDate: Date
  -endDate: Date
}

class ApprovalRequest {
  -id: int
  -requestDate: Date
  -status: Status (pending, approved, rejected)
  -trajectory: Trajectory
}

class Category {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -priceFactor: float
}

class MENSOUser {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -homeAddress: String
  -officeAddress: String
  -workingHours: String
  -mensocardId: String
}

class Trip {
  -id: int
  -date: Date
  -time: Time
  -line: Line
  -user: MENSOUser
}

class Invoice {
  -id: int
  -month: Date
  -totalAmount: float
  -discount: float
  -user: MENSOUser
  -trips: List<Trip>
}

class Payment {
  -id: int
  -amount: float
  -date: Date
  -invoice: Invoice
}

' Define associations and multiplicity

Bus "1" --> "1" Line
Line "1" --> "*" Trajectory
Trajectory "1" --> "*" ApprovalRequest
Trajectory "1" --> "0..1" Bus

MENSOUser "1" --> "*" Trip
Trip "1" --> "1" Line
Trip "1" --> "1" MENSOUser

Invoice "1" --> "*" Trip
Invoice "1" --> "0..1" Payment
Payment "1" --> "1" Invoice

' Define enums

enum Status {
  approved
  suspended
  cancelled
  pending
  rejected
}

enum CategoryType {
  local
  regional
  intercity
}
@enduml

---

### 📌 Explanation of Key Elements:
- **`Bus`** has a line number and can be assigned to a trajectory.
- **`Line`** groups multiple `Trajectory` objects and belongs to a `Category`.
- **`Trajectory`** can go through an approval process and may be in various statuses (`approved`, `suspended`, `cancelled`).
- **`ApprovalRequest`** tracks each request made by the company to the town authorities.
- **`Category`** determines the pricing factor used for the MENSO ticket.
- **`MENSOUser`** holds personal data and is linked to trips and invoices.
- **`Trip`** records the use of the MENSO card and links to both a user and a line.
- **`Invoice`** is generated monthly based on trips and applies a possible discount.
- **`Payment`** is associated with an invoice and represents payment made.

